    "title": "Doughnut recall forecast counts",
    "prompt": "Implement a scoped PBI in Doughnut: As a learner, I want the Recall page to show how many recall items are due now and how many more would be loaded from the next 3, 7, and 14 days, so that I can decide whether to continue recalling without blindly clicking each load-more button.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- The recall API exposes forecast counts for due windows 0, 3, 7, and 14 days using the same timezone and half-day alignment rules as current recall loading.\n- Forecast counts are monotonic by window and exclude deleted/removed memory trackers.\n- Existing Load more from next 3/7/14 days behavior remains compatible.\n- The Recall page done state/buttons display forecast counts without breaking treadmill mode or existing current-session progress.\n- Add or update targeted backend and frontend tests where practical.\n- Keep edits scoped to recall DTO/service/controller/UI/composable/test surfaces; do not rewrite unrelated recall flows.",
